# Database Engineer — Bunyan

## Migration Governance

### File Integrity

- Migrations in `backend/database/migrations/`
- Naming: `YYYY_MM_DD_HHMMSS_verb_noun_table.php`
- Verbs: `create`, `add`, `modify`, `drop`, `rename`
- Never modify existing migrations — forward-only
- Always include `down()` rollback

### Lock Risk Analysis (MySQL)

| Risk   | Operations                                          |
| ------ | --------------------------------------------------- |
| LOW    | `ADD COLUMN` (nullable), `DROP COLUMN`              |
| MEDIUM | `ADD COLUMN WITH DEFAULT`, `ADD INDEX`              |
| HIGH   | `ALTER COLUMN TYPE`, `ADD NOT NULL` on large tables |

Block HIGH-risk without mitigation strategy.

### Foreign Key Safety

- All relationships must have explicit foreign keys
- Cascade deletes carefully considered (soft delete preferred)
- Index foreign key columns

## Query Performance

- Eager load relationships (prevent N+1)
- Use `select()` to limit columns
- Query scopes for reusable conditions
- Chunking for large datasets
- Index: WHERE, ORDER BY, JOIN columns

## MySQL-Specific

- `InnoDB` engine for all tables
- `utf8mb4` charset for Arabic text
- Composite indexes for multi-column queries
- Fulltext indexes for Arabic text search
- Use `EXPLAIN` for slow queries

## Core Schema

| Table                   | Key Relationships                       |
| ----------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| users                   | roles (many-to-many), projects          |
| projects                | phases, users (polymorphic)             |
| phases                  | tasks (optional), projects, reports     |
| tasks                   | phases, reports                         |
| workflow_configurations | projects (nullable for global)          |
| approval_rules          | workflow_configurations                 |
| reports                 | phases/tasks (polymorphic), users       |
| transactions            | users, projects                         |
| products                | categories, order_items                 |
| orders                  | users, order_items, projects (nullable) |

## Conventions

- Soft deletes: users, projects, phases, tasks, products, orders
- Audit columns: `created_at`, `updated_at`, `created_by`, `updated_by`

